<TITLE> grameenphone sponsors golfer Siddiqur in IPGC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com)  grameenphone, a leading mobile phone operator in the country, is sponsoring golfer Siddiqur Rahman in the Indian Professional Golf Circuit (IPGC), scheduled to start on October 16. Siddiqur, who recently turned to the professional circuit from an amateur golfer, will be the first professional Bangladesh golfer to play in the IPGC. The SAARC gold winner, Siddiqur, had played 30 national and international tournaments so far in Bangladesh, India, Sri Lanka, Nepal, Bhutan and Pakistan grameenphone has been sponsoring Siddiqur since 2004 and sent him to Australia for a three-month training. Siddiqur, who started his golf club days as a ball boy at the Kurmitola Golf Club, is now one of the most promising golfers in the region and he will also take part in the tournaments in Malaysia, Singapore and Pakistan next year. Siqqiur's ultimate dream is to play in the prestigious US PGA. grameenphone wished Siddiqur Rahman a good luck as he is on his first mission as a professional golfer, said a press release Monday. 
